Template: blockhost-broker/private-key-action
Type: select
Choices: generate, provide, skip
Default: generate
Description: Ethereum private key setup
 The broker needs an Ethereum private key to deploy contracts and sign transactions.
 .
 Choose how to set up your private key:
  - generate: Create a new random key
  - provide: Enter an existing key
  - skip: Configure manually later

Template: blockhost-broker/private-key
Type: password
Description: Ethereum private key
 Enter your Ethereum private key (hex format, with or without 0x prefix).
 .
 This key will be stored securely with restricted permissions.

Template: blockhost-broker/wallet-address
Type: note
Description: Wallet address created
 Your wallet address is: ${ADDRESS}
 .
 This address will be used for contract deployment and operations.

Template: blockhost-broker/fund-wallet
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Wallet needs funding
 Your wallet has insufficient funds for contract deployment.
 .
 Current balance: ${BALANCE}
 Required minimum: 0.01 ETH (Sepolia testnet)
 .
 Please send Sepolia ETH to: ${ADDRESS}
 .
 You can get free Sepolia ETH from:
  - https://sepoliafaucet.com
  - https://www.alchemy.com/faucets/ethereum-sepolia
 .
 Have you sent funds to the wallet?

Template: blockhost-broker/deploy-contract
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Deploy BrokerRequests contract?
 Would you like to deploy a new BrokerRequests contract?
 .
 This contract handles allocation requests from clients.
 You need one deployed contract per broker instance.
 .
 If you already have a contract deployed, choose No and provide the address.

Template: blockhost-broker/existing-contract
Type: string
Description: Existing BrokerRequests contract address
 Enter the address of your existing BrokerRequests contract.
 .
 Format: 0x followed by 40 hexadecimal characters
 Example: 0x43880eA324BF7842A72a9ed0680B3dd1cD6CD7C8

Template: blockhost-broker/contract-deployed
Type: note
Description: Contract deployed successfully
 BrokerRequests contract deployed at: ${CONTRACT_ADDRESS}
 .
 This has been saved to your configuration.

Template: blockhost-broker/ipv6-interface
Type: select
Choices: ${INTERFACES}
Description: IPv6 interface selection
 Select the IPv6 interface to use for the broker.
 .
 The broker will allocate prefixes from this interface's address range.

Template: blockhost-broker/ipv6-prefix
Type: string
Description: Upstream IPv6 prefix
 Enter the upstream IPv6 prefix for allocations.
 .
 This is the prefix range from which client allocations will be made.
 .
 Format: address/prefix_length (e.g., 2001:db8::/48)

Template: blockhost-broker/allocation-size
Type: select
Choices: 64, 112, 120, 124, 128
Default: 64
Description: Allocation size (prefix length)
 Select the prefix length for client allocations.
 .
  /64: Standard (18 quintillion addresses per host)
  /112: Medium (65,536 addresses per host)
  /120: Small (256 addresses per host)
  /124: Minimal (16 addresses per host)
  /128: Single address per host

Template: blockhost-broker/broker-ipv6
Type: string
Description: Broker IPv6 address
 Enter the broker's own IPv6 address.
 .
 This should be an address within your upstream prefix that the broker
 will use for its own communication.
 .
 Example: 2001:db8::1

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-interface
Type: string
Default: wg-broker
Description: WireGuard interface name
 Enter the name for the WireGuard interface.

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-port
Type: string
Default: 51820
Description: WireGuard listen port
 Enter the UDP port for WireGuard to listen on.

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-endpoint
Type: string
Description: Public endpoint (hostname:port)
 Enter the public hostname or IP address and port that clients
 will use to connect to this broker.
 .
 Format: hostname:port or ip:port
 Example: broker.example.com:51820

Template: blockhost-broker/upstream-interface
Type: string
Description: Upstream network interface for NDP proxy
 Enter the upstream network interface name for NDP proxy.
 .
 This is the interface connected to your IPv6 provider (e.g., sit1 for a
 SIT tunnel, he-ipv6 for Hurricane Electric, or eth0 for native IPv6).
 .
 NDP proxy entries will be added on this interface so that your provider
 can route traffic to allocated client addresses.
 .
 Leave blank to skip NDP proxy configuration.

Template: blockhost-broker/setup-complete
Type: note
Description: Setup complete
 Blockhost Broker has been configured.
 .
 Configuration file: /etc/blockhost-broker/config.toml
 .
 Next steps:
  1. Register your broker in BrokerRegistry smart contract
  2. Start the service: systemctl enable --now blockhost-broker
  3. Monitor logs: journalctl -u blockhost-broker -f
